<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 04 at 5:39PM CDT  by NWS Wichita</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Cowley
County through 615 PM CDT...
At 538 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Chilocco, or 7 miles south of Arkansas City, moving northeast at 45
mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Arkansas City, Winfield, Burden, Dexter, Maple City and Strother
Field Airport.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
